Sentencas: A composite braze, consisting of Ag-Cu-Ti braze alloy and particulate Al2TiO5 filler, was used to produce metal/braze/metal and metal/braze/YSZ joints to seal and interconnect metal-supported SOFC membranes.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of Al2TiO5 to the braze alloy lowers the coefficient of thermal expansion (CTE) of the resulting composite sufficiently so as to produce joints in which the YSZ does not crack due to CTE mismatch.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Optimization of the reactive element (Ti) loading is discussed with regard to its effect on electrolyte conductivity.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electronic conductivity, sealing ability, and strength of the braze alloy remain acceptable after complete oxidation at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Joints were also tested in air/fuel dual atmosphere environment at 700 degrees C. After this exposure, the joint remains hermetically sealed, and no significant degradation of the joint was observed.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This is in contrast to a free-standing foil of the braze alloy, which failed upon dual atmosphere exposure.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The composite braze material was used to seal a metal-supported thin-film YSZ cell.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The sealed cell was thermally cycled 30 times very rapidly without any deterioration of the open circuit voltage.
Titulo: A braze system for sealing metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells
